        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Functions {code}Zend_Date::getSunrise(){code} and {code}Zend_Date::getSunset(){code} return \"1970-12-08T00:00:00-03:00\" for any date\/time and city.\n\nThe problem occoured in revision 2729:\n\nWhere it says {code}'Zend_Date::TIMESTAMP'{code}, it should say {code}Zend_Date::TIMESTAMP{code} (without the quotes, otherwise {code}Zend_Date::set(){code} does not recognize the constant)."
