        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21194",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Interesting... \n\nI am doing this:\n{code}\n        $date = new Zend_Date(1010101010);\n        $date->setTimezone('Indian\/Maldives');\n\n        $result = $date->getSunset(Zend_Date_Cities::City('vienna'));\n        echo $result->get(Zend_Date::W3C);\n{code}\n\nand it returns this:\n{code}\n'2002-01-04T20:09:59+05:00'\n{code}\n\nSo in my eyes it works.\n\nI think you made a mistake by using getSunset as static which is not true. This should throw an error by php as this method is not static and needs an instance.\n\nIf not, please give a reproducable example, so we can verify the problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-19T04:40:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-19T04:40:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21213",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nadameu",
                        "name": "nadameu",
                        "displayName": "Paulo Roberto Maurici Junior",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually I didn't use the static method.\n\nBut now I tested it in a separate file, outside my MVC, and it worked.\n\nThe problem only happens when i use the following code before the calculation:\n\n{code}Zend_Date::setOptions(array('format_type' => 'php'));{code}\n\nShouldn't it still be ok to do date calculations even though i set 'format_type' to 'php' ?\n\nBy the way, thanks for the quick response.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nadameu",
                        "name": "nadameu",
                        "displayName": "Paulo Roberto Maurici Junior",
